          <td bgcolor="" valign="top"><!-- #BeginEditable "Body" --> 
            <table width=100% border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>
<tr><td width=1><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_01.gif" width=6 height=6></td><td width=100% background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_02.gif"></td>
<td width=1><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_03.gif" width=6 height=6></td></tr>
<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_04.gif"><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/clear.gif" height=35 width=1></td>
<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><input type="hidden" name="PHPSESSID" value="...328fedb22570524062aeb1303" /><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/heroclix/treports/treports.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/vs/treports/treports.php'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/treports/treports.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/treports/treports.php'>Ophidian 2350</option><option value='/magic/treports/treports.php'>The Wastelands</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Longshot @ Continentals 6/27/04<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(5.00)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=5711'>Michael "Longshot" Mendoza</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=5711&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> July 12, 2004</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> Well my computer died on me so I have only just now finished part 2 of my Origins report.  I had wanted to finish this right after part 1 because my memory would have been better.<br />
<br />
As you no doubt read in part 1 of my Origins report, I finished 4-4 in the PSE using men/elf and Nazgul.  I really liked my fellowship so I kept that the same for Continentals.  I just replaced the Nazgul with my corsair shadow.  After my experience with the Witch-King and Blade with Ferny getting beat down all the time, I decided against using Castamir/Halberd and focused more on swarming with my corsairs.  I still played 4 castamirs though.<br />
<br />
Lisa changed her deck as well.  Ryan Jones and I helped her fix her besieger deck, and she changed her shadow to man/elf instead of valiant Rohan.  Robbie also fixed his deck, but he did it largely on his own.  He must have gone through 5 different variants on his deck before he finally made it into twilight nazgul corruption.  His fellowship remained the same for the most part.  Ryan changed his shadow to easterlings and John ran with corsairs (as opposed to their sauron corruption decks from the PSE).<br />
<br />
After Day 1 of the PSE Jonesy, Patch, Pete, and I went out for some drinks.  There was a large contingent of card players (way too many for me to remember who they were, I just remember Sullivan stole an onion ring from me and shared it with Patchell, and I remember Seth M. and Will D. were there too) up on the 2nd level of the bar, and I went up just to say hi but it looked like they were never going to be served by anyone.  Patch stayed up there a while.  Jonesy, Pete, and I just hung out at a table on the 1st level, close by where Brochu and his squad was.  After eating and/or drinking, we leave the bar and head to our hotel.<br />
<br />
Patchell plays Day 1 of Continentals and manages to qualify for Day 2 of continentals.  The rest of us do various other things because we all have byes already.  Lisa and I play .hack, Ryan plays Marvel, and Robbie and Pete play in Day 2 of the PSE (and both unfortunately get eliminated first round).  Later, Robbie and I play some Settlers of Catan.<br />
<br />
Patch, Lisa, Robbie and I leave and go back to the hotel (Ryan and Pete stayed at the con to watch some games).  Lisa and Robbie playtest while Patch and I head out and get a 15 pack of beers, some SkyBlue (for Lisa) and some food.  We drink and play all night and I beat Patch 5 times in 5 games, all with my Nazgul.  He used 3 different decks but lost with all of them.  But of course, he won in the tournament and he didn’t let me forget that.  I keep trying to make a new shadow but Patch insists on challenging my Nazgul deck cuz he says it sucks (and it does).  Later that night (much later) Pete and Ryan walk in and help us with our decks.  Anyways, I still have no intention of playing Nazgul, and after a long night of drinking Lisa, Robbie, and I go back to our room and that is when I take out the Nazgul and put in corsairs, since it is the only shadow I have built.  At about 5 AM I crash.<br />
<br />
I wake up at 730 AM or so and get my decklist ready, making a few changes as I am writing (though I was so tired I have no idea what they were).  So we get to the convention and this time its Kim Logie who is the level 4 judge.  She calls the pairings and we start the first of 6 games.  62 people were there I think for this one.  Many players decided not to play in Continentals, so it was smaller than the PSE turnout.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
GAME 1 v Brian Fred’s man/elf and Moria<br />
He bids 3 and goes first.  He plays Dervorin & Aragorn and moves.  He moves to 2 and I play a few boats.  He moves again, I play a Black Numenorean, and I have a few tokens out so I play my pump to overwhelm Glorfindel.  I also double to 3 easy, but he stacks a Host on Swarms.  On his turn he plays Tale of Gilgalad on Lego and moves, I play a Castamir and exert to play a fierce guy to get some tokens and initiative.  Castamir gets shot down and Aragorn takes a couple wounds.<br />
<br />
I move to 4 and face some orcs and stop there.  Brian moves to 5 and I have 13 twilight or so.  I play castamir and use all my boats, ending up with 6 corsairs vs his 5 companions.  Frodo has to fight but I have a +6 pump in hand, so I win there.  Win (3 points).<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
GAME 2 v Max Bouchard’s dwarves/corsairs<br />
He bids to go first.  He plays some dwarf stuff, draws his 4 cards, and moves.  I play some boats, he moves again.  On my turn, I play Aragron and move.  I get to see Castamir and halberd.  He eats 2 guys.  His turn he just moves to 4 and stops.  I don’t do much.  I play Faramir and Elendil, trying to rebuild my shattered fellowship.  Another castamir and halberd.  Oh well, this game is over.  Two more guys go away.<br />
<br />
He moves to site 5 where I actually drop some guys that do some damage to him, but then he plays Blood Runs Chill and I have to lose most of my boats (I chose to keep my minions out).  He stops.  I move to 4 and face some cheap corairs, so I figure I finally get a break.  But Isildur’s got to fight, and I can’t add burdens since I’m at site 4.  So I exert my only 3 companions and I get hit with red wrath to kill one and the other dies in the fierce.  Yay.  So now I’m down to Isildur.  He moves to 6 and stops, I move to 5 and die.  Loss (4 points).<br />
<br />
Worst: I didn’t draw any of my Gondor Bowmen or Last alliances early.  Either of those are the only things that save me from castamir with Halberd in the early game.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
GAME 3 v Justin Collins’ man/elf and Easterlings<br />
He bids to go first.  This was a brutal game.  We both double easily to 3, but I got my corsair boats out early, and hit him hard at site 4 and 5.  At both sites he lost companions, but he always had extras to replace them.  Faramir replaced the fallen Greenleaf at site 4, and Boromir and Derufin replaced Aragorn and Faramir when they died at 5.  Then Boromir and Derufin both died at site 6.<br />
<br />
His shadow was beating on me too.  His Captain/polearm/bow combo got the stops on me.  I drew Faramir but no Elrond so Faramir couldn’t always fight.  The point is, I had to stay behind him and I could never double.  So we’re both sitting at site 7, and time is winding down.  Justin moves to site 8 and time is called.  I play my minions and use my ships and manage to make it so that everyone has to fight, but I have no pumps in my hand.  However, I do have Corsair gunners, and lots of tokens.  So I make everyone fierce, and Frodo survives the first skirmish but I kill a companion so Frodo has to fight 2 guys in the fierce and dies.  That was close, because I was at site 7 and him at 8 so he would have gotten the win had I not killed him there.  Win (9 points).<br />
<br />
Best: Discarding Elrond twice with my Lookouts.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
GAME 4 v Reed Mascola’s dwarves/sauron grind<br />
First off, sorry Reed I’m not going to post my deck.  I know you wanted to see it, but I just don’t have the energy to do it.  Reed is 3-0 at this point so I am paired up since I am 2-1.<br />
<br />
I bid to go first.  I double to 3 while he plays an Archer Troop and Orc Bowmen along the way.  I discard Vilya because I have no Elrond, and I draw Elrond.  He moves to 2 and I play a Castamir and he stops there.  I play Elrond and Scroll, then I toss my Scroll to get Vilya back.  Now I feel a little safer against the Grind, and I still have 2 Sentinels coming up.<br />
<br />
He plays Shoulder to Shoulder and Elrond.  I play another Castamir on him at site 3, and he stops.  I move to site 5, playing Sentinels to get rid of a Bowmen and Watching Eye, but he has 2 Hates to kill off Greenleaf.  I stop, he moves to 4, and I just play cheap corsairs but he stops anyways.  I move to 6, and he has 2 more Hates to kill off Glorfindel.  Now I’m mad.  :)<br />
<br />
He moves to 5 and I think he moves again to 6, but I can’t recall exactly.  I’m not doing much damage to him, because he’s not giving much twilight anymore.  In any case, I move to site 7 and again to 8.  Then he moves, and I move again to 9 for the win and he doesn’t have any real minions to play so we end the game as soon as I move to 9.  Win (10 points).<br />
<br />
Best: Elrond/Vilya early.  In fact, Vilya came too early, lol.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
GAME 5 v Mat Brochu’s dwarves/easterlings<br />
Again I get paired up to play someone who is 4-0 while I am 3-1.  I guess that’s good for SoS totals, right?<br />
<br />
He bids to go first.  He doubles to 3, I play some boats but he gets the Blood Runs Chill to wipe the board clean.  He discards a Raider Bow, so I know the easterling Captain will be coming down at site 2.  I get Aragorn and Last Alliance out, and sure enough I have to face a Captain with polearm and bow, and small Hope of course.  Aragorn takes a wound to start, and then Glorfindel dies in the fierce.  I stop.<br />
<br />
Brochu plays 2 companions (greenleaf and sam) moves to 4, and I play a bunch of cheap corsairs and a couple boats.  I take some axes and discard some cards to get initiative back.  He kills Sam off and I actually do some wounds to his dwarves because I have two +6 pumps that go back on my deck.  He’s got the Honeds of course so no one is killed (other than Sam).  I play lots of stuff (including Anduril) and move to 3 and am stopped again this time by an Army with bow and polearm.  Aragorn takes a couple wounds and gets red wrathed so he’s exhausted now.  I stop at 3.<br />
<br />
Brochu moves to 5.  I drop big corsairs this time, and I’ve got initiative with my boats so the Black Numenorean can get to work.  Plus of course I still have pumps in hand.  I kill some dwarf (Uri?  Sindri?  I don’t recall) and he stops.  I move to site 4 and lose Derufin because he’s got another Captain and polearm and bow.  Ok, I shouldn’t have to see this guy for very much longer right?  That’s 4 bows and 3 polearms now.  I stop at 4.<br />
<br />
Brochu plays 2 or 3 more companions and moves to site 6.  Castamir comes down, and exerts once to play a corsair (Gunner I think).  I may have been the only person running the corsair gunners.  Anyways, he’s got Merry as one of his companions and a Honed so Durin is not getting overwhelmed.  He stops at 6 with 6 or 7 companions.  I get Faramir with Last Alliance so I’m in better shape now.  I see another Captain with polearm at site 5, but Aragorn takes him once, then Faramir, then Elrond heals Faramir, and I move again to 6.  He played a couple more easterlings, but I used Greenleaf and Gondor Bowmen to shoot them down.  His Vision From Afar adds a burden though.  Faramir takes the Captain twice and I finally catch up to him at long last at site 6.<br />
<br />
Ok, so Brochu moves to site 7.  I play Castamir and a couple corsairs and I start drawing cards for my site 7.  I draw Enquea and play him.  He had Eowyn so I couldn’t kill anyone with Enquea.  And I wounded Durin rather than kill Eowyn.  Time was winding down and I was rushing things.  That was dumb of me, I should have killed Eowyn.  Anyways, I end up killing merry and Eowyn and Legolas too.  Yeah, those pumps were still happening every turn.  It’s the only way I could win skirmishes!  He discards ring of fury to heal everyone and stops.<br />
<br />
I double to 8, and now he’s rushing because time is winding down.  We know he can’t kill me; he’s seen his big minions and polearms and bows already.  And Isildur is holding Narsil and Last Alliance so he’s a power 14 (16 if he puts the ring on).  So I double to 8.  He plays a companion and moves to 8, I drop the most minions I possibly can, then I stack my deck a little with my ship during the regroup phase.  I need to stack minions!  I also discard a war galley to add twilight and use Fierce In Despair to take out Linnar.  And he moves again as time is called.  I play enough minions so that everyone has to fight.  So of course you all know what that means.  Two +6 pumps on Gimli end the game, even though he has Honed.  What a close game.  Win (13 points)<br />
<br />
Best: Playing Brochu.  I came to Origins to play the best!<br />
<br />
<br />
GAME 6 v Pat Sullivan’s dwarves/Morgul Orcs<br />
I bid to go first.  I flood the pool and move to site 2 (keeping initiative barely), but he plays nothing.  I call the bluff and move to 3.  He plays Cantea to add a threat.  He moves to site 2 and stops, and I realize he wasn’t bluffing, he’s got a handful of shadow!  My fellowship is looking ok, with Elrond and Vilya out for healing and some other stuff, but I decide to add threats to draw cards anyway.  And I draw all shadow.  Yay.  Those threats bite me when I move to site 4, since I see 8 freakin’ minions.  Isildur takes some wounds and burdens also.  And I think Glorfindel dies here because I had 5 threats, so Pat took off 4 threats to overwhelm Glorfindel with that Orc that pumps himself.<br />
<br />
Pat moves to 3 easily, and may have played a Blood Runs Chill to clear my boats.  I think he did.  Pretty much every dwarf deck I played against did that to me at site 3.  I play sam to take some burdens off, and a Scroll to improve my resistance.  I also play Narsil on Elendil (who already had Last Alliance), so he is power 15 baby!  I make the move limit +1 but I face another squad of minions at site 5.  I don’t think anyone died, but I have to stop.  Pat moves to site 4, and I move to my site 6 for some MUCH needed healing.<br />
<br />
Pat takes the opportunity to double to 6, as I don’t draw much in the way of minions.  I move to 7 and stop, and time is winding down.  Pat moves to 7, but I play nothing, even though I have a good shadow hand.  I don’t want to time out here.  Pat thinks but decides to stop as well.  Now I need to double, but my hand is all shadow!  Oh well, I move and Pat drops another SQUAD, and yeah that’s all capitals because it was bigger than his other squads.  How?  Because he pulled Nazgul for dirt cheap with his site 8.  .  And then during archery phase time is called.  Oh well.  He could have let me double to 9 and get 3 extra threats from site 9, but then he wouldn’t get those cheap nazgul from site 8.  Tough call either way.  The extra threats might have done it since I didn’t really have anywhere to put those threats.<br />
<br />
Anyways, he plays at site 8 and I assign and Isildur ends up fighting 2 Destroyers and Gollum.  That’s power 17 to my 9.  I kill off a companion to pop the threats so the Destroyers can’t pump and that’s game.  Barely.  Win (16 points).<br />
<br />
Best: Playing Pat.  I came to Origins to play the best competition like him.  He’s a great opponent.<br />
Worst: Timing out.  It’s the only game I timed out all weekend, and he just dropped such squads on me that I always had to think about the assignments.  Luckily I assigned wisely every time.  You can’t really play too fast in a game where you always have 7-8 minions to assign per site (and with self-pumps like “remove to a burden to be +3” it makes it even harder).<br />
<br />
<br />
Lisa had been 3-0, but lost her last 3 games to finish 3-3.  She had to face Dalton, who she defeated, but she lost to Alex K. and Brochu’s girlfriend.  Robbie finished 4-2 with a timed win that his opponent wouldn’t concede as a full win.<br />
<br />
So what they do is take the top 8 seeds and have them play a single elimination tournament.  I finish 5-1 and in the 2nd seed, so I’m happy.  Michael Perucca was 6-0 in the 1st seed.  My joy ends though when I discover who I have to play in the top 8 elimination round.<br />
<br />
<br />
Top 8 Single Elimination Round<br />
Vs Max Bouchard<br />
Aw jeez.  First round I have to play the only guy who beat me (and quite solidly, I might add).  I figure I have to go first if I want to win.  I bid 4 to his 2.  I think about starting Sam, but I decide against it because I want Legolas and a possible Gondor Bowmen to defend against a site 2 castamir and halberd.  I also decide that Greenleaf and Sam is too weak of a start.  Again, I don’t draw my Gondor Bowmen or Last Alliance, so I have to play nothing and just move, since I can’t afford to have castamir ruin my day again.  He plays some ships so I move into site 3 without fear of castamir.<br />
<br />
He also doubles to 3 easily.  I play some boats but he has Blood Runs Chill to take them out.  Sadly, I don’t draw much going into site 4.  And remember I have 4 burdens.  Yeah I was wishing I had started Sam.  Anyways, he uses those 4 burdens and pumps in his hand to overwhelm 2 guys and I am down to Isildur and Faramir.  He moves to 4 and stops.  I play Sam (a little late) and move to 5.  He kills everyone but Isildur, however, Isildur had to fight and is up to 4 burdens again.  He moves to 6 and stops, and I don’t draw anything to help me move to 6 so I just concede the game.  Isildur can’t even fight since he had 4 burdens on him and no Scroll on table.  Loss.<br />
<br />
Best: Max is a great opponent, and it really was good playing him.  I really need to give better competition next time though.  My fellowship never bends over like that even against other decks that are identical.<br />
Worst: Had I drawn Last Alliance or Bowmen….<br />
<br />
Getting eliminated first round always sucks, but I was really tired anyways and my stomach was telling me to stop playing cards and get some food.  Max made it all the way to the semifinals against Alex K. from Canada, but Alex won and is the North American Champion!  Just don’t grab my @$$ next time dude.  You scare me.  I don’t know what games you play in Canada, but here in SF we don’t go in for those back-door shenanigans.<br />
<br />
I got 3 packs as prizes and we all headed home to relax and start packing to go home.  Lisa and I watch some mobster movie I never heard of with Jennifer Tilly and Gina Gershon in it...those two were getting it on in the movie!  Robbie said &quot;Are you gonna add Red Wrath?&quot; at some point in his sleep.  So I said &quot;No, Whirling Strike.&quot;<br />
<br />
Lisa and Robbie and I all went to the airport and we parted company with Robbie there.  Lisa and I boarded our flight to O’Hare in Chicago, but it was delayed and we missed our connecting flight to SF.  So we got back to SF much later than planned, and we were tired.  Comicon is next!  Thanks for reading.<br />
<br />
Props to:<br />
Patchell for the rides and playtesting.  It was a fun weekend.<br />
Lisa and Robbie for all the trades, playtesting and just being cool.<br />
Alex and Robbie for teaching me to play Settlers.<br />
All the west coast players for representing at Origins.<br />
Everyone who read this, and liked it.<br />
Corsairs for being a THOUSAND times better than the Nazgul.<br />
<br />
Slops to:<br />
Dunya Ertan (again) for being an idiot.<br />
Nazgul for letting me down in the PSE.<br />
O’Hare Airport <br></font></blockquote><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php?id=5117&view=1&PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php?PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/lotr/main/join.php?PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'> become a registered member</a></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
